Foreign direct investment into  South
Korea  increased 17 percent in the first quarter, the Ministry of
Knowledge Economy said in an e-mailed statement today.  Investment totaled $2.35 billion in the three months to
March 31, up from $2.01 billion a year earlier, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
